19/09/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- UN police have arrested four Kosovo Serbs accused of committing war crimes during the 1998-1999 conflict in the province, the detainees' family told international media Sunday (18 September). The suspects were identified as three brothers -- Zivorad, Slobodan and Milovan Maksimovic -- and their uncle, Ljubisa Peric. All are from the village of Novi Badovac near Pristina. (Politika, B92 - 19/09/05; AFP - 18/09/05)
